#. type: heading **
#: configuration.org:75
#, no-wrap
msgid "Flake"
msgstr "Flake"

#. type: paragraph
#: configuration.org:77
msgid ""
"This flake manages NixOS, nix-darwin, and home-manager configurations for "
"multiple machines across different platforms (macOS, Linux, Android). It "
"uses flake-parts for modular organization and includes tooling for "
"development, code formatting, and pre-commit hooks."
msgstr ""
"このflakeはmacOS、Linux、Androidの複数プラットフォームにまたがるマシンの"
"NixOS、nix-darwin、home-manager設定を管理しています。flake-partsによるモ"
"ジュール構成を採用し、開発、コードフォーマット、pre-commitフックのためのツー"
"ルも含んでいます。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: configuration.org:87
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  description = \"dotfiles\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: configuration.org:90
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"inputs = {\n"
"  <<nixpkgs>>\n"
"  <<nixpkgs-stable>>\n"
"  <<flake-parts>>\n"
"  <<flake-utils>>\n"
"  <<darwin>>\n"
"  <<home-manager>>\n"
"  <<nixos-wsl>>\n"
"  <<nix-on-droid>>\n"
"  <<disko>>\n"
"  <<impermanence>>\n"
"  <<lanzaboote>>\n"
"  <<nixos-facter-modules>>\n"
"  <<comin>>\n"
"  <<sops-nix>>\n"
"  <<tsnsrv>>\n"
"  <<git-hooks>>\n"
"  <<treefmt-nix>>\n"
"  <<nix-colors>>\n"
"  <<nix-wallpaper>>\n"
"  <<brew-nix>>\n"
"  <<claude-desktop>>\n"
"  <<edgepkgs>>\n"
"  <<emacs-overlay>>\n"
"  <<firefox-addons>>\n"
"  <<mcp-servers>>\n"
"  <<niri-flake>>\n"
"  <<nur-packages>>\n"
"  <<simple-wol-manager>>\n"
"  <<zen-browser>>\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: configuration.org:130
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"nixConfig = {\n"
"  <<nix-config>>\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: configuration.org:134
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  outputs =\n"
"    { self, flake-parts, ... }@inputs:\n"
"    flake-parts.lib.mkFlake { inherit inputs; } {\n"
"      <<outputs>>\n"
"    };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: configuration.org:142
#, no-wrap
msgid "Inputs"
msgstr "入力"

#. type: paragraph
#: configuration.org:144
msgid "External flake dependencies."
msgstr "外部flake依存関係です。"

#. type: paragraph
#: configuration.org:146
msgid ""
"To minimize evaluation time caused by dependency graph bloat, almost all "
"flakes are configured to follow the same nixpkgs and other common inputs "
"wherever possible."
msgstr ""
"依存関係グラフの肥大化による評価時間の増加を抑えるため、ほぼすべてのflakeで同"
"一のnixpkgsや共通のinputをfollowするように設定しています。"

#. type: heading ****
#: configuration.org:149
#, no-wrap
msgid "Core"
msgstr "コア"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: configuration.org:151 configuration.org:170
#, no-wrap
msgid "nixpkgs"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: configuration.org:153
msgid "https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in QUOTE
#: configuration.org:156
msgid "Nix Packages collection & NixOS"
msgstr "Nixパッケージコレクション & NixOS"

#. type: paragraph
#: configuration.org:159
msgid ""
"The primary package set. Using =nixos-unstable-small= instead of =nixos-"
"unstable= for faster channel updates. The =-small= variant skips some less "
"critical CI tests, allowing new package versions to propagate faster while "
"maintaining stability for core packages."
msgstr ""
"メインのパッケージセットです。チャンネル更新を高速にするため、=nixos-"
"unstable= ではなく=nixos-unstable-small= を使用しています。=-small= バリアン"
"トは重要度の低い一部のCIテストを省略するため、コアパッケージの安定性を維持し"
"つつ新しいパッケージバージョンをより早く取得できます。"

#. type: paragraph
#: configuration.org:163
msgid ""
"For channel selection guidance, see https://nix.dev/concepts/faq.html#which-"
"channel-branch-should-i-use"
msgstr ""
"チャンネルの選び方については https://nix.dev/concepts/faq.html#which-channel-"
"branch-should-i-use を参照してください。"

#. type: paragraph
#: configuration.org:165
msgid "Channel status can be checked at https://status.nixos.org/"
msgstr "チャンネルの状態は https://status.nixos.org/ で確認できます。"

#. type: paragraph
#: configuration.org:167
msgid ""
"Using =git+https://= with =shallow=1= instead of =github:= for slightly "
"faster file extraction on large repositories like nixpkgs."
msgstr ""
"nixpkgsのような大規模リポジトリでのファイル展開をわずかに高速化するため、"
"=github:= の代わりに=git+https://= と =shallow=1= を使用しています。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: configuration.org:172
#, no-wrap
msgid "nixpkgs.url = \"git+https://github.com/nixos/nixpkgs?shallow=1&ref=nixos-unstable-small\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: configuration.org:175 configuration.org:180
#, no-wrap
msgid "nixpkgs-stable"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: configuration.org:177
msgid ""
"Provides stable packages when unstable has build failures or regressions. "
"Mainly used by the =stable= overlay (see [[file:overlays/configuration.org]"
"[overlays/configuration.org]]) for packages that are broken in unstable."
msgstr ""
"unstableでビルド失敗やリグレッションが発生した際に安定版パッケージを提供しま"
"す。主にunstableで壊れているパッケージに対して=stable= overlay"
"（[[file:overlays/configuration.org][overlays/configuration.org]]参照）で使用"
"されています。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: configuration.org:182
#, no-wrap
msgid "nixpkgs-stable.url = \"git+https://github.com/nixos/nixpkgs?shallow=1&ref=nixos-25.05\";"
msgstr ""

