#. type: heading ***
#: applications/emacs/init.org:957
#, no-wrap
msgid "project.el"
msgstr "project.el"

#. type: paragraph
#: applications/emacs/init.org:959
msgid ""
"Register all repositories cloned by ghq (https://github.com/x-motemen/ghq) "
"as projects."
msgstr ""
"ghq（https://github.com/x-motemen/ghq）でクローンしたリポジトリをすべてプロ"
"ジェクトとして登録します。"

#. type: paragraph
#: applications/emacs/init.org:961
msgid ""
"Specifically, directories under =~/src/$ACCOUNT/$VCS_HOST/$OWNER/$REPO=."
msgstr ""
"具体的には、=~/src/$ACCOUNT/$VCS_HOST/$OWNER/$REPO= 配下のディレクトリが対象"
"です。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: applications/emacs/init.org:964
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(defun my/sync-project-list ()\n"
"  \"Find all projects under ~/src and synchronize the project-list-file.\"\n"
"  (interactive)\n"
"  (let* (;; 1. Retrieve directory list as a string using find command\n"
"         (command (format \"find %s -mindepth 4 -maxdepth 4 -type d\"\n"
"                          (expand-file-name \"~/src\")))\n"
"         (dir-list-string (shell-command-to-string command))\n"
"         ;; 2. Split string by newlines and exclude empty lines to create a list\n"
"         (dirs (split-string dir-list-string \"\\n\" t)))"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: applications/emacs/init.org:974
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
";; 3. Build file contents in a temporary buffer\n"
"(with-temp-buffer\n"
"  (insert \";;; -*- lisp-data -*-\\n\")\n"
"  (insert \"(\\n\")\n"
"  (dolist (dir dirs)\n"
"    (insert (format \" (\\\"%s/\\\")\\n\" dir)))\n"
"  (insert \")\\n\")"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: applications/emacs/init.org:982
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
";; 4. Write the built contents to file\n"
"(write-file project-list-file))))"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: applications/emacs/init.org:985
#, no-wrap
msgid "(my/sync-project-list)"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: applications/emacs/init.org:988
msgid ""
"Sort the project list by modification time, placing recently updated "
"projects first."
msgstr ""
"プロジェクト一覧を更新日時順にソートし、最近更新されたプロジェクトを先頭に表"
"示します。"

#. type: paragraph
#: applications/emacs/init.org:990
msgid ""
"Using advice instead of sorting in =my/sync-project-list= ensures that "
"projects are sorted by their current mtime at selection time, not at file "
"generation time.  This keeps the order fresh even during long Emacs sessions."
msgstr ""
"=my/sync-project-list= 内でソートするのではなくadviceを使うことで、ファイル生"
"成時ではなく選択時の現在のmtimeでソートされます。これにより、長時間のEmacs"
"セッション中でも常に最新の順序が維持されます。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: applications/emacs/init.org:995
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(defun my/sort-projects-by-mtime (projects)\n"
"  \"Sort PROJECTS by modification time, most recent first.\"\n"
"  (sort projects\n"
"        (lambda (a b)\n"
"          (let ((time-a (file-attribute-modification-time\n"
"                         (file-attributes a)))\n"
"                (time-b (file-attribute-modification-time\n"
"                         (file-attributes b))))\n"
"            (time-less-p time-b time-a)))))"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: applications/emacs/init.org:1005
#, no-wrap
msgid "(advice-add 'project-known-project-roots :filter-return"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "disable some bars"
msgstr "不要なバーを消す"

#. type: paragraph
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:5
msgid ""
"The tool bar duplicates functionality already accessible via keybindings and "
"the menu bar, while the vertical scroll bar wastes horizontal space without "
"providing useful navigation—line numbers and modeline indicators are more "
"precise.  Setting these in ~default-frame-alist~ rather than calling ~tool-"
"bar-mode~ / ~scroll-bar-mode~ avoids a brief flash of the bars during "
"startup before the modes disable them."
msgstr ""
"ツールバーはキーバインドやメニューバーから既にアクセスできる機能と重複してお"
"り、垂直スクロールバーは有用なナビゲーションを提供せず水平方向のスペースを浪"
"費します。行番号やモードラインの表示の方がより正確です。~tool-bar-mode~ / "
"~scroll-bar-mode~ を呼ぶのではなく ~default-frame-alist~ で設定することで、"
"モードが無効化される前にバーが一瞬表示されるちらつきを防ぎます。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(push '(tool-bar-lines . 0) default-frame-alist)\n"
"(push '(vertical-scroll-bars) default-frame-alist)"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "turn off the annoying bell"
msgstr "煩わしいベルが鳴らないようにする"

#. type: paragraph
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:19
msgid ""
"The default audible bell is distracting and provides no actionable "
"information.  Replacing it with ~ignore~ silences it entirely; a visual bell "
"(~visible-bell~) was not chosen because the screen flash is equally "
"disruptive."
msgstr ""
"デフォルトのビープ音は注意を散漫にし、有用な情報を提供しません。~ignore~ に置"
"き換えることで完全に消音します。ビジュアルベル（~visible-bell~）は画面のフ"
"ラッシュも同様に邪魔なため採用しませんでした。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "(setq ring-bell-function 'ignore)"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "disable backup files"
msgstr "ファイルのバックアップを作らないようにする"

#. type: paragraph
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:30
msgid ""
"Emacs already skips backup files for version-controlled files by default "
"(~vc-make-backup-files~ is ~nil~), but files outside of a repository still "
"produce backups.  Since virtually all editing happens in Git-managed trees, "
"the remaining cases are rare enough that the clutter outweighs the safety "
"net.  Auto-save files are likewise redundant when unsaved work can be "
"recovered through Git stashes or reflog."
msgstr ""
"Emacsはデフォルトでバージョン管理下のファイルのバックアップを作成しません"
"（~vc-make-backup-files~ が ~nil~）が、リポジトリ外のファイルにはバックアップ"
"が作られます。実質的にすべての編集はGit管理下のツリーで行うため、残りのケース"
"は稀であり、散らかりの方が安全策としての価値を上回ります。自動保存ファイルも"
"同様に、未保存の作業はGitのstashやreflogで復元できるため不要です。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(setq make-backup-files nil)\n"
"(setq auto-save-default nil)"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading **
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:42
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "disable lock files"
msgstr "ロックファイルを作らないようにする"

#. type: paragraph
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:44
msgid ""
"Lock files (~.#filename~) prevent concurrent editing across multiple Emacs "
"instances, but in a single-instance workflow they only clutter the working "
"directory and interfere with file watchers and build tools."
msgstr ""
"ロックファイル（~.#filename~）は複数のEmacsインスタンス間での同時編集を防止し"
"ますが、シングルインスタンスのワークフローでは作業ディレクトリを散らかし、"
"ファイル監視やビルドツールの妨げになるだけです。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: applications/emacs/early-init.org:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "(setq create-lockfiles nil)"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword OPTIONS
#: overlays/configuration.org:3 modules/configuration.org:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "^:{}"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading *
#: overlays/configuration.org:5 modules/configuration.org:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "概要"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:7
msgid ""
"This file defines nixpkgs overlays for patching broken packages, pinning "
"specific versions, and adding local workarounds. Each overlay modifies the "
"package set to address issues that would otherwise block the system build or "
"cause runtime problems."
msgstr ""
"このファイルでは、壊れたパッケージの修正、特定バージョンのピン留め、ローカル"
"な回避策の追加のためのnixpkgs overlayを定義しています。各overlayはパッケージ"
"セットを変更し、システムのビルドを妨げたり実行時の問題を引き起こす課題に対処"
"します。"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:11
msgid ""
"For details on overlay mechanics (=final: prev:= pattern, composition order, "
"etc.), see [[https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#chap-overlays][nixpkgs "
"overlay documentation]]."
msgstr ""
"overlayの仕組み（=final: prev:= パターン、合成順序など）の詳細は [[https://"
"nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#chap-overlays][nixpkgs overlayドキュメント]]"
"を参照してください。"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:14
msgid ""
"Overlays are organized into four categories based on their purpose and "
"expected lifetime:"
msgstr ""
"overlayは目的と想定される存続期間に基づいて4つのカテゴリに分類されています："

#. type: plain list -
#: overlays/configuration.org:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*stable*: Packages fetched from nixpkgs-stable when broken in unstable and the fix would\n"
"trigger excessive rebuilds or is too complex to patch locally."
msgstr ""
"*stable*: unstableで壊れており、修正すると大量のリビルドが発生するか、\n"
"ローカルでパッチするには複雑すぎる場合にnixpkgs-stableから取得するパッケージ。"

#. type: plain list -
#: overlays/configuration.org:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*temporary-fix*: Local overrides (e.g., disabling tests) that don't require a different\n"
"nixpkgs version. Remove once fixed upstream."
msgstr ""
"*temporary-fix*: 別のnixpkgsバージョンを必要としないローカルオーバーライド\n"
"（例: テストの無効化）。アップストリームで修正されたら削除します。"

#. type: plain list -
#: overlays/configuration.org:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "*pre-release*: Alpha, beta, or pre-release packages for testing before they land in nixpkgs."
msgstr "*pre-release*: nixpkgsに入る前にテストするためのアルファ版、ベータ版、プレリリースパッケージ。"

#. type: plain list -
#: overlays/configuration.org:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*patches*: Workarounds not suitable for upstream contribution (e.g., locale-specific fixes,\n"
"local tooling shims). Expected to remain indefinitely."
msgstr ""
"*patches*: アップストリームへの貢献に適さない回避策（例: ロケール固有の修正、\n"
"ローカルツールのshim）。恒久的に残る想定です。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{ inputs }:\n"
"{\n"
"  <<stable>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<temporary-fix>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<pre-release>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  <<patches>>\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: overlays/configuration.org:42 overlays/configuration.org:48
#, no-wrap
msgid "stable"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:44
msgid ""
"Fetch packages from nixpkgs-stable when broken in unstable. This includes "
"cases where the upstream fix would trigger excessive rebuilds, or where the "
"issue is too complex to patch locally."
msgstr ""
"unstableで壊れている場合にnixpkgs-stableからパッケージを取得します。アップス"
"トリームの修正が大量のリビルドを引き起こす場合や、ローカルでパッチするには複"
"雑すぎる場合が該当します。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:50
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"stable = final: prev: {\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: overlays/configuration.org:54 overlays/configuration.org:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "temporary-fix"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:56
msgid ""
"Local overrides for packages that build but have failing tests or minor "
"issues.  Unlike the =stable= overlay, these don't require fetching packages "
"from a different nixpkgs branch. We simply override specific attributes "
"(like =doCheck=) on the existing packages. Remove these overrides once the "
"issues are fixed upstream."
msgstr ""
"ビルドはできるがテストが失敗したり軽微な問題があるパッケージのローカルオー"
"バーライドです。=stable= overlayとは異なり、別のnixpkgsブランチからパッケージ"
"を取得する必要はありません。既存パッケージの特定の属性（=doCheck= など）を"
"オーバーライドするだけです。アップストリームで問題が修正されたらこれらのオー"
"バーライドを削除します。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:63
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"temporary-fix = final: prev: {\n"
"  <<python313-package-set>>\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: overlays/configuration.org:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "Python313 package set"
msgstr "Python313パッケージセット"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:70
msgid "Override problematic Python packages using =packageOverrides=."
msgstr ""
"=packageOverrides= を使用して問題のあるPythonパッケージをオーバーライドしま"
"す。"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:72
msgid ""
"Python packages in nixpkgs form an interconnected dependency graph. The "
"=packageOverrides= mechanism ensures that when a package is overridden, all "
"dependent packages automatically see the modified version. This is essential "
"for consistency—a direct overlay override (e.g., =python313Packages.foo "
"= ...=) would only affect top-level access, leaving internal dependencies "
"using the original broken version."
msgstr ""
"nixpkgsのPythonパッケージは相互に接続された依存関係グラフを形成しています。"
"=packageOverrides= の仕組みにより、パッケージがオーバーライドされると、依存す"
"るすべてのパッケージが自動的に変更後のバージョンを参照します。これは一貫性の"
"ために不可欠です。直接的なoverlayオーバーライド（例: =python313Packages.foo "
"= ...=）ではトップレベルのアクセスにしか影響せず、内部の依存関係は元の壊れた"
"バージョンを使い続けてしまいます。"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:78
msgid ""
"See [[https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#overriding-python-packages]"
"[nixpkgs Python documentation]] for details."
msgstr ""
"詳細は[[https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#overriding-python-packages]"
"[nixpkgs Pythonドキュメント]]を参照してください。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: overlays/configuration.org:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "python313-package-set"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:82
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"python313 = prev.python313.override {\n"
"  packageOverrides = pyfinal: pyprev: {\n"
"    <<rapidocr-onnxruntime>>\n"
"    <<lxml-html-clean>>\n"
"  };\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: overlays/configuration.org:90 overlays/configuration.org:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "rapidocr-onnxruntime"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:92
msgid ""
"The test suite causes a segmentation fault during execution. The root cause "
"is still under investigation."
msgstr ""
"テストスイートの実行中にセグメンテーションフォールトが発生します。根本原因は"
"まだ調査中です。"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:95
msgid ""
"This package is pulled in as a transitive dependency. Runtime functionality "
"has been verified to work correctly in actual use, so disabling the test "
"suite is a safe workaround."
msgstr ""
"このパッケージは推移的な依存関係として取り込まれています。実際の使用でランタ"
"イム機能が正しく動作することは確認済みのため、テストスイートの無効化は安全な"
"回避策です。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:100
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rapidocr-onnxruntime = pyprev.rapidocr-onnxruntime.overridePythonAttrs (_: {\n"
"  doCheck = false;\n"
"});"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: overlays/configuration.org:105 overlays/configuration.org:114
#, no-wrap
msgid "lxml-html-clean"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:107
msgid ""
"Tests fail due to breaking changes in libxml2 2.14, which modified how "
"certain DOM operations handle whitespace and entity encoding. These changes "
"cause test assertions to fail even though the actual HTML cleaning "
"functionality works correctly."
msgstr ""
"libxml2 2.14の破壊的変更により、特定のDOM操作における空白文字やエンティティエ"
"ンコーディングの処理方法が変更されたためテストが失敗します。実際のHTMLクリー"
"ニング機能は正しく動作しているにもかかわらず、テストのアサーションが失敗しま"
"す。"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:111
msgid ""
"Tracked upstream in [[https://github.com/fedora-python/lxml_html_clean/"
"issues/24][fedora-python/lxml_html_clean#24]].  Remove this override once "
"the test suite is updated for libxml2 2.14 compatibility."
msgstr ""
"アップストリームでは [[https://github.com/fedora-python/lxml_html_clean/"
"issues/24][fedora-python/lxml_html_clean#24]]で追跡されています。テストスイー"
"トがlibxml2 2.14互換に更新されたらこのオーバーライドを削除します。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:116
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"lxml-html-clean = pyprev.lxml-html-clean.overridePythonAttrs (_: {\n"
"  doCheck = false;\n"
"});"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: overlays/configuration.org:121 overlays/configuration.org:127
#, no-wrap
msgid "pre-release"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:123
msgid ""
"Overlay for testing alpha, beta, or pre-release versions of packages before "
"they land in nixpkgs. Useful for evaluating release candidates, nightly "
"builds, or packages pending upstream review. Once a package is available in "
"nixpkgs, remove it from this overlay."
msgstr ""
"nixpkgsに入る前のアルファ版、ベータ版、プレリリース版パッケージをテストするた"
"めのoverlayです。リリース候補、ナイトリービルド、アップストリームのレビュー待"
"ちパッケージの評価に便利です。nixpkgsで利用可能になったら、このoverlayから削"
"除します。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:129
#, no-wrap
msgid "pre-release = final: prev: { };"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: overlays/configuration.org:132 overlays/configuration.org:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "patches"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:134
msgid "Workarounds that are not suitable for upstream contribution."
msgstr "アップストリームへの貢献に適さない回避策です。"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:136
msgid ""
"These patches address issues that upstream would likely not accept—either "
"because they are specific to this configuration (e.g., locale settings), "
"bypass intended behavior, or solve problems in unconventional ways. Unlike "
"=temporary-fix=, these are expected to remain indefinitely."
msgstr ""
"これらのパッチは、アップストリームが受け入れないであろう問題に対処します。こ"
"の設定固有のもの（例: ロケール設定）、意図された動作を迂回するもの、または非"
"標準的な方法で問題を解決するものが該当します。=temporary-fix= とは異なり、恒"
"久的に残る想定です。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:143
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"patches = final: prev: {\n"
"  <<gh-dash>>\n"
"  <<command-line-tools-shim>>\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: keyword NAME
#: overlays/configuration.org:149 overlays/configuration.org:162
#, no-wrap
msgid "gh-dash"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:151
msgid ""
"The preview pane renders incorrectly when =LANG=ja_JP.UTF-8= is set. The "
"issue stems from gh-dash's terminal width calculation, which miscounts the "
"display width of certain UTF-8 characters (particularly CJK characters and "
"some emoji). This causes text wrapping and alignment to break."
msgstr ""
"=LANG=ja_JP.UTF-8= が設定されているとプレビューペインが正しく描画されません。"
"gh-dashの端末幅計算が特定のUTF-8文字（特にCJK文字や一部の絵文字）の表示幅を"
"誤ってカウントすることが原因です。これによりテキストの折り返しと配置が崩れま"
"す。"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:156
msgid ""
"Setting =LANG=C.UTF-8= forces ASCII-compatible width calculations while "
"preserving UTF-8 encoding support, which fixes the rendering issue. We use "
"=writeShellApplication= to create a wrapper that sets this environment "
"variable before invoking the real binary."
msgstr ""
"=LANG=C.UTF-8= を設定するとUTF-8エンコーディングのサポートを維持しつつASCI互"
"換の幅計算が強制され、描画の問題が修正されます。=writeShellApplication= を"
"使って、実際のバイナリを呼び出す前にこの環境変数を設定するラッパーを作成して"
"います。"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:160
msgid ""
"Reported upstream in [[https://github.com/dlvhdr/gh-dash/issues/316][dlvhdr/"
"gh-dash#316]]."
msgstr ""
"アップストリームでは [[https://github.com/dlvhdr/gh-dash/issues/316][dlvhdr/"
"gh-dash#316]]で報告済みです。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:164
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gh-dash =\n"
"  (final.writeShellApplication {\n"
"    name = \"gh-dash\";\n"
"    text = ''\n"
"      LANG=C.UTF-8 ${final.lib.getExe prev.gh-dash} \"$@\"\n"
"    '';\n"
"  }).overrideAttrs\n"
"    { pname = \"gh-dash\"; };"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: overlays/configuration.org:174
#, no-wrap
msgid "mkShim"
msgstr "mkShim"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:176
msgid ""
"Shim utility for providing stub implementations of macOS Command Line Tools."
msgstr "macOS Command Line Toolsのスタブ実装を提供するshimユーティリティです。"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:178
msgid ""
"On darwin systems without Xcode Command Line Tools installed, invoking "
"commands like =cc= or =python3= triggers an annoying system popup prompting "
"installation.  These shims intercept such calls and either delegate to Nix-"
"provided tools or return appropriate exit codes, suppressing the popup and "
"preventing spurious build failures."
msgstr ""
"Xcode Command Line Toolsがインストールされていないdarwinシステムでは、=cc= "
"や =python3= などのコマンドを実行するとインストールを促す煩わしいシステムポッ"
"プアップが表示されます。これらのshimはそのような呼び出しをインターセプトし、"
"Nixが提供するツールに委譲するか適切な終了コードを返すことで、ポップアップを抑"
"制し不要なビルド失敗を防ぎます。"

#. type: paragraph
#: overlays/configuration.org:183
msgid ""
"See [[file:../pkgs/mkShim/][pkgs/mkShim]] for the implementation details and "
"list of shimmed commands."
msgstr ""
"実装の詳細とshim化されたコマンドの一覧は [[file:../pkgs/mkShim/][pkgs/"
"mkShim]]を参照してください。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: overlays/configuration.org:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "command-line-tools-shim"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: overlays/configuration.org:187
#, no-wrap
msgid "inherit (final.callPackage ../pkgs/mkShim { }) mkShim commandLineToolsShim;"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:7
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "This file defines custom NixOS and nix-darwin modules that extend the "
#| "standard module system.  Each module addresses specific use cases or "
#| "provides opinionated defaults not available upstream."
msgid ""
"This file defines custom modules that extend the standard NixOS, nix-darwin, "
"and home-manager module systems. Each module addresses specific use cases or "
"provides opinionated defaults not available upstream."
msgstr ""
"このファイルでは、標準のモジュールシステムを拡張するカスタムNixOSおよびnix-"
"darwinモジュールを定義しています。各モジュールは特定のユースケースに対応する"
"か、アップストリームにない独自のデフォルトを提供します。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:11
msgid ""
"Modules are organized by functional domain (e.g., Shell, Networking, Version "
"Control) rather than by module system target. When a domain contains both "
"system-level and user-level configuration, subheaders separate them "
"explicitly."
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:17
msgid ""
"Nix package manager and nixpkgs configuration. These modules are shared "
"across NixOS and nix-darwin, providing consistent Nix behavior on all "
"machines."
msgstr ""
"Nixパッケージマネージャーとnixpkgsの設定です。これらのモジュールはNixOSとnix-"
"darwinで共有され、すべてのマシンで一貫したNixの動作を提供します。"

#. type: heading ***
