msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1281
#, no-wrap
msgid "Force Push Safety"
msgstr "強制プッシュの安全対策"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1283
msgid ""
"=push.useForceIfIncludes= enables a safety check for force pushes: git "
"verifies that the local branch includes the remote's current tip before "
"allowing a force push. This prevents accidentally overwriting commits pushed "
"by others since the last fetch, which =--force-with-lease= alone cannot "
"catch if the remote ref was updated in the background (e.g., by lazygit's "
"periodic fetch or a background =git fetch=)."
msgstr ""
"=push.useForceIfIncludes= は強制プッシュの安全チェックを有効にします。gitは"
"ローカルブランチがリモートの現在のtipを含んでいるか確認してから強制プッシュを"
"許可します。これにより、最後のfetch以降に他の人がプッシュしたコミットを誤って"
"上書きすることを防ぎます。=--force-with-lease= だけでは、リモートrefがバック"
"グラウンドで更新された場合（例: lazygitの定期的なfetchやバックグラウンドの"
"=git fetch=）に検出できません。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1289
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-push-safety"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1291
#, no-wrap
msgid "push.useForceIfIncludes = true;"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1294
#, no-wrap
msgid "URL Rewriting"
msgstr "URLの書き換え"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1296
msgid ""
"=url.\"git@github.com:\".pushInsteadOf= rewrites push URLs from HTTPS to "
"SSH. This allows =git clone https://github.com/...= to work without SSH "
"(useful in CI or ephemeral environments) while ensuring pushes always use "
"SSH authentication, avoiding the need for personal access tokens."
msgstr ""
"=url.\"git@github.com:\".pushInsteadOf= はプッシュURLをHTTPSからSSHに書き換え"
"ます。これにより=git clone https://github.com/...= がSSHなしで動作し（CIや一"
"時的な環境で有用）、プッシュは常にSSH認証を使用するため、パーソナルアクセス"
"トークンが不要になります。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1301
msgid ""
"In practice, [[*GitHub CLI][=gh=]] provides its own credential helper that "
"handles HTTPS authentication transparently, so this rewrite rule may not be "
"exercised for GitHub repositories. It is retained as an intentional fallback "
"for environments where =gh= is not available."
msgstr ""
"実際には、[[*GitHub CLI][=gh=]]が独自の認証ヘルパーを提供し、HTTPS認証を透過"
"的に処理するため、この書き換えルールはGitHubリポジトリでは実行されないかもし"
"れません。=gh= が利用できない環境のための意図的なフォールバックとして保持され"
"ています。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1305
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-url-rewrite"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1307
#, no-wrap
msgid "url.\"git@github.com:\".pushInsteadOf = \"https://github.com/\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1310
#, no-wrap
msgid "Commit Signing"
msgstr "コミット署名"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1312
msgid ""
"SSH-based commit signing. SSH keys were chosen over GPG because SSH keys are "
"already required for push authentication, eliminating the need to manage a "
"separate GPG keychain.  Git's SSH signing support (added in Git 2.34) "
"provides the same integrity guarantees as GPG signing with simpler key "
"management — one key pair for both authentication and signing."
msgstr ""
"SSHベースのコミット署名です。SSHキーはプッシュ認証にすでに必要なため、別途GPG"
"キーチェーンを管理する必要がなくなることからGPGよりSSHキーが選ばれました。Git"
"のSSH署名サポート（Git 2.34で追加）は、よりシンプルな鍵管理でGPG署名と同じ整"
"合性保証を提供します。認証と署名の両方に1つの鍵ペアで対応できます。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1317
msgid ""
"GitHub has [[https://github.blog/changelog/2022-08-23-ssh-commit-"
"verification-now-supported/][supported SSH commit verification since August "
"2022]], and since [[https://github.blog/changelog/2024-11-12-persistent-"
"commit-signature-verification-now-in-public-preview/][November 2024]] "
"verification results are persisted server-side. This persistent verification "
"eliminates the primary concern with SSH signing — that key rotation could "
"invalidate historical signatures — which was GPG's main advantage for long-"
"term identity assurance."
msgstr ""
"GitHubは[[https://github.blog/changelog/2022-08-23-ssh-commit-verification-"
"now-supported/][2022年8月からSSHコミット検証をサポート]]しており、[[https://"
"github.blog/changelog/2024-11-12-persistent-commit-signature-verification-"
"now-in-public-preview/][2024年11月]]から検証結果がサーバー側に永続化されるよ"
"うになりました。この永続的検証により、SSH署名の主な懸念点であった鍵のローテー"
"ションによる過去の署名の無効化が解消され、長期的なIDの保証におけるGPGの主な利"
"点がなくなりました。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1322
msgid ""
"In the future, migrating to a keyless solution like [[https://github.com/"
"sigstore/gitsign][gitsign]] (Sigstore-based signing)  would further simplify "
"the workflow by removing key management entirely. This is pending GitHub's "
"native support for Sigstore verification."
msgstr ""
"将来的には、[[https://github.com/sigstore/gitsign][gitsign]]（Sigstoreベース"
"の署名）のようなキーレスソリューションに移行することで、鍵管理を完全に不要に"
"しワークフローをさらに簡素化できます。GitHubがSigstore検証をネイティブサポー"
"トするのを待っている状態です。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1326
msgid ""
"=signByDefault = true= ensures all commits are signed without requiring =git "
"commit -S=, preventing unsigned commits from slipping through."
msgstr ""
"=signByDefault = true= はすべてのコミットを=git commit -S= なしで署名し、未署"
"名のコミットが紛れ込むのを防ぎます。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1329
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-signing"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1331
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"signing = {\n"
"  format = \"ssh\";\n"
"  key = \"~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub\";\n"
"  signByDefault = true;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1338
#, no-wrap
msgid "Global Ignores"
msgstr "グローバルIgnore"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1340
msgid ""
"Patterns that should never be committed across all repositories. These are "
"global ignores rather than per-repo =.gitignore= entries because they "
"reflect personal tooling choices that should not be imposed on collaborators."
msgstr ""
"すべてのリポジトリでコミットすべきでないパターンです。リポジトリごとの "
"=.gitignore= エントリではなくグローバルignoreとしているのは、個人的なツール選"
"択を反映しており、共同作業者に押し付けるべきではないためです。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1344
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-ignores"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1346
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ignores = [\n"
"  <<git-ignores-os>>\n"
"  <<git-ignores-dev>>\n"
"  <<git-ignores-workflow>>\n"
"  <<git-ignores-private>>\n"
"];"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1354
#, no-wrap
msgid "OS Artifacts"
msgstr "OSアーティファクト"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1356
msgid ""
"macOS Finder metadata files. Present in the global ignore because this is a "
"cross-platform dotfiles repository used on both Linux and macOS."
msgstr ""
"macOS Finderのメタデータファイルです。LinuxとmacOSの両方で使用されるクロスプ"
"ラットフォームなdotfilesリポジトリのため、グローバルignoreに含めています。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1359
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-ignores-os"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1361
#, no-wrap
msgid "\".DS_Store\""
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1364
#, no-wrap
msgid "Development Environment"
msgstr "開発環境"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1366
msgid "Artifacts generated by development tools that should remain local:"
msgstr "ローカルに留めるべき開発ツールが生成するアーティファクトです："

#. type: plain list -
#: modules/configuration.org:1370
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"=.aider*= matches aider's conversation history and configuration files. These contain\n"
"session-specific context and should not leak into repositories."
msgstr ""
"=.aider*= はaiderの会話履歴と設定ファイルにマッチします。\n"
"セッション固有のコンテキストを含むため、リポジトリに漏れるべきではありません。"

#. type: plain list -
#: modules/configuration.org:1373
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"=.direnv=, =.envrc=: direnv state and configuration. Each project may define its own\n"
"=.envrc=, but since this repository uses flake-based devshells, the =.envrc= files are\n"
"auto-generated and should not be committed."
msgstr ""
"=.direnv=、=.envrc=: direnvの状態と設定。各プロジェクトが独自の\n"
"=.envrc= を定義できますが、このリポジトリではflakeベースのdevshellを使用するため、\n"
"=.envrc= ファイルは自動生成されコミットすべきではありません。"

#. type: plain list -
#: modules/configuration.org:1374
#, no-wrap
msgid "=.ipynb_checkpoints=: Jupyter Notebook autosave files."
msgstr "=.ipynb_checkpoints=: Jupyter Notebookの自動保存ファイル。"

#. type: plain list -
#: modules/configuration.org:1376
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"=.pre-commit-config.yaml=: Managed per-project by devshell environments rather than committed,\n"
"to avoid version conflicts across contributors with different tool versions."
msgstr ""
"=.pre-commit-config.yaml=: コミットではなくdevshell環境でプロジェクトごとに管理し、\n"
"ツールバージョンの異なるコントリビューター間のバージョン競合を避けます。"

#. type: plain list -
#: modules/configuration.org:1377
#, no-wrap
msgid "=.vscode/=: Editor-specific settings that vary per developer."
msgstr "=.vscode/=: 開発者ごとに異なるエディター固有の設定。"

#. type: plain list -
#: modules/configuration.org:1378
#, no-wrap
msgid "=__pycache__/=: Python bytecode cache, regenerated on each run."
msgstr "=__pycache__/=: Pythonバイトコードキャッシュ。実行ごとに再生成されます。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1379
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-ignores-dev"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1381
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\".aider*\"\n"
"\".direnv\"\n"
"\".envrc\"\n"
"\".ipynb_checkpoints\"\n"
"\".pre-commit-config.yaml\"\n"
"\".vscode/\"\n"
"\"__pycache__/\""
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1390
#, no-wrap
msgid "Workflow"
msgstr "ワークフロー"

#. type: plain list -
#: modules/configuration.org:1393
#, no-wrap
msgid "=.worktree=: Marker file used by git worktree workflows."
msgstr "=.worktree=: git worktreeワークフローで使用されるマーカーファイル。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1394
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-ignores-workflow"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1396
#, no-wrap
msgid "\".worktree\""
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1399
#, no-wrap
msgid "Private Notes"
msgstr "プライベートノート"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1401
msgid ""
"=.private/= is a directory for personal notes, LLM context files, and other "
"local-only documentation that should never be shared."
msgstr ""
"=.private/= は個人的なメモ、LLMコンテキストファイル、その他の共有すべきでない"
"ローカル専用のドキュメントのためのディレクトリです。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1404
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-ignores-private"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1406
#, no-wrap
msgid "\".private/\""
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1409
#, no-wrap
msgid "Scalar"
msgstr "Scalar"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1411
msgid ""
"[[https://git-scm.com/docs/scalar][Scalar]] optimizes git performance for "
"large repositories. Enabled specifically for the nixpkgs repository, which "
"contains over 600,000 commits and benefits significantly from Scalar's "
"background maintenance (prefetch, commit-graph, loose-objects) and "
"filesystem monitor integration."
msgstr ""
"[[https://git-scm.com/docs/scalar][Scalar]]は大規模リポジトリのgitパフォーマ"
"ンスを最適化します。600,000件以上のコミットを持つnixpkgsリポジトリ向けに特に"
"有効化されており、Scalarのバックグラウンドメンテナンス（prefetch、commit-"
"graph、loose-objects）とファイルシステムモニターの統合から大きな恩恵を受けま"
"す。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1416
msgid ""
"The Scalar module (=programs.git.scalar=) is a custom home-manager module "
"defined in [[file:home-manager/git-scalar.nix][home-manager/git-scalar.nix]] "
"that configures git's built-in performance optimizations (multipack index, "
"preload index, untracked cache, fsmonitor)."
msgstr ""
"Scalarモジュール（=programs.git.scalar=）は[[file:home-manager/git-"
"scalar.nix][home-manager/git-scalar.nix]]で定義されたカスタムhome-managerモ"
"ジュールで、gitの組み込みパフォーマンス最適化（multipack index、preload "
"index、untracked cache、fsmonitor）を設定します。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1420
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-scalar"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1422
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"scalar = {\n"
"  enable = true;\n"
"  repo = [ \"${config.programs.git.settings.ghq.root}/github.com/natsukium/nixpkgs\" ];\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1428
#, no-wrap
msgid "GitHub CLI"
msgstr "GitHub CLI"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1430
msgid ""
"[[https://cli.github.com/][gh]] (GitHub CLI) is enabled alongside git "
"because it provides a credential helper ([[https://nix-community.github.io/"
"home-manager/options.xhtml#opt-programs.gh.gitCredentialHelper.enable]"
"[=programs.gh.gitCredentialHelper.enable=]], on by default) that "
"transparently handles HTTPS authentication for GitHub repositories. This is "
"why the [[*URL Rewriting][=pushInsteadOf=]] setting may not be exercised in "
"practice — =gh='s auth context covers both fetch and push over HTTPS."
msgstr ""
"[[https://cli.github.com/][gh]]（GitHub CLI）はgitとともに有効化されていま"
"す。認証ヘルパー（[[https://nix-community.github.io/home-manager/"
"options.xhtml#opt-programs.gh.gitCredentialHelper.enable]"
"[=programs.gh.gitCredentialHelper.enable=]]、デフォルトで有効）を提供し、"
"GitHubリポジトリのHTTPS認証を透過的に処理するためです。これが[[*URLの書き換"
"え][=pushInsteadOf=]]設定が実際には実行されないかもしれない理由です。=gh= の"
"認証コンテキストはHTTPS経由のfetchとpushの両方をカバーします。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1436
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-gh"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1438
#, no-wrap
msgid "programs.gh.enable = true;"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1441
#, no-wrap
msgid "Delta"
msgstr "Delta"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1443
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/dandavison/delta][delta]] provides syntax-highlighted "
"diffs in the terminal with line numbers and side-by-side view support. "
"Chosen for its clean visual presentation."
msgstr ""
"[[https://github.com/dandavison/delta][delta]]はターミナルでシンタックスハイ"
"ライト付きのdiffを提供し、行番号やサイドバイサイド表示をサポートします。ク"
"リーンな視覚的表現が選定理由です。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1446
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-delta"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1448
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"programs.delta = {\n"
"  enable = true;\n"
"  enableGitIntegration = true;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1454
#, no-wrap
msgid "Difftastic"
msgstr "Difftastic"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1456
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/Wilfred/difftastic][Difftastic]] is a structural diff "
"tool that operates at the AST level rather than comparing lines. It "
"understands that moving a function or renaming a variable is a single "
"semantic change, not a block of deletions and insertions. This is "
"particularly valuable for JSX refactoring, indentation shifts, and nested "
"tag restructuring, where line-based diffs produce noisy, hard-to-read output."
msgstr ""
"[[https://github.com/Wilfred/difftastic][Difftastic]]は、行単位の比較ではなく"
"AST（抽象構文木）レベルで動作する構造的差分ツールです。関数の移動や変数のリ"
"ネームを、削除と挿入のブロックではなく、単一の意味的変更として認識します。こ"
"れはJSXのリファクタリング、インデントの変更、ネストされたタグの再構成において"
"特に有用で、行ベースの差分ではノイズが多く読みにくい出力になる場面で力を発揮"
"します。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1462
msgid ""
"Both difftastic and [[*Delta][delta]] are kept because they serve "
"complementary roles: delta enhances git's built-in line diffs with syntax "
"highlighting for everyday operations (=git diff=, =git log=), while "
"difftastic is reached for via [[*Lazygit][lazygit]] when structural "
"understanding matters."
msgstr ""
"difftasticと[[*Delta][delta]]の両方を併用しているのは、それぞれ補完的な役割を"
"持つためです。deltaは日常的な操作（=git diff=、=git log=）でGitの組み込み行差"
"分にシンタックスハイライトを追加し、difftasticは構造的な理解が重要な場面で"
"[[*Lazygit][lazygit]]経由で使用します。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1467
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-difftastic"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1469
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"programs.difftastic = {\n"
"  enable = true;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1474
#, no-wrap
msgid "Lazygit"
msgstr "Lazygit"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1476
msgid ""
"[[https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit][Lazygit]] is a terminal UI for "
"git. A TUI was chosen over raw git commands for interactive operations like "
"staging individual hunks, interactive rebase, and conflict resolution, where "
"the visual feedback loop significantly reduces errors. Previously used "
"gitui, but switched to lazygit for its broader feature set — gitui's "
"performance advantage did not materialize in practice, and it lacked several "
"workflow-critical operations."
msgstr ""
"[[https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit][Lazygit]]はGitのターミナルUIで"
"す。個別のhunkのステージング、インタラクティブリベース、コンフリクト解決と"
"いった対話的操作では、視覚的なフィードバックループがエラーを大幅に減らすた"
"め、生のGitコマンドではなくTUIを選択しました。以前はgituiを使用していました"
"が、より広い機能セットを持つlazygitに移行しました。gituiのパフォーマンス上の"
"優位性は実際には現れず、ワークフローに不可欠な操作がいくつか欠けていました。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1482
msgid ""
"Performance degrades noticeably on large repositories like nixpkgs, but the "
"ergonomics and active development make it a trusted part of the workflow "
"despite this tradeoff."
msgstr ""
"nixpkgsのような大規模リポジトリではパフォーマンスが顕著に低下しますが、操作性"
"と活発な開発により、このトレードオフにもかかわらずワークフローの信頼できる一"
"部となっています。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1485
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-lazygit"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1487
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"programs.lazygit = {\n"
"  enable = true;\n"
"  settings = {\n"
"    <<lazygit-gui>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1492
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <<lazygit-git>>\n"
"  };\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1497
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "UI"
msgid "GUI"
msgstr "UI"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1499
msgid "Enable Nerd Font icons in the lazygit interface for visual clarity."
msgstr ""
"視認性向上のため、lazygitのインターフェースでNerd Fontアイコンを有効にしま"
"す。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1501
#, no-wrap
msgid "lazygit-gui"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1503
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gui = {\n"
"  showIcons = true;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1508
#, no-wrap
msgid "Git Integration"
msgstr "Git連携"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1510
msgid ""
"=overrideGpg = true= tells lazygit to run git commands inline instead of "
"spawning a subprocess for GPG/SSH signing. By default, lazygit defers to a "
"subprocess so the user can type a passphrase interactively. However, this "
"subprocess mode prevents lazygit from orchestrating interactive rebase "
"internally — rewording, reordering, or editing any commit other than HEAD is "
"[[https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit/issues/1146][disabled entirely]] "
"because the rebase would trigger multiple signing prompts that lazygit "
"cannot handle mid-rebase. With =overrideGpg = true=, lazygit assumes the "
"signing agent (ssh-agent, macOS Keychain) caches the passphrase, so no "
"interactive prompt is needed and all rebase operations work normally."
msgstr ""
"=overrideGpg = true= は、lazygitにGPG/SSH署名用のサブプロセスを生成する代わり"
"にGitコマンドをインラインで実行するよう指示します。デフォルトでは、lazygitは"
"ユーザーが対話的にパスフレーズを入力できるようサブプロセスに委譲します。しか"
"し、このサブプロセスモードではlazygitが内部でインタラクティブリベースを制御で"
"きなくなります。リベース中に複数の署名プロンプトが発生し、lazygitがそれを処理"
"できないため、HEAD以外のコミットのリワード、並べ替え、編集が[[https://"
"github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit/issues/1146][完全に無効化]]されます。"
"=overrideGpg = true= を設定すると、lazygitは署名エージェント（ssh-agent、"
"macOS Keychain）がパスフレーズをキャッシュしていると想定するため、対話的プロ"
"ンプトが不要になり、すべてのリベース操作が正常に動作します。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1519
msgid ""
"The pager configuration integrates both [[*Delta][delta]] and [[*Difftastic]"
"[difftastic]] into lazygit's diff views.  Delta provides syntax-highlighted "
"line diffs (=--dark --paging=never= since lazygit handles its own paging), "
"and difftastic is available as the external diff command for [[*Difftastic]"
"[structural comparison]]."
msgstr ""
"ページャー設定により、[[*Delta][delta]]と[[*Difftastic][difftastic]]の両方が"
"lazygitの差分ビューに統合されます。Deltaはシンタックスハイライト付きの行差分"
"を提供し（lazygitが独自にページングを行うため =--dark --paging=never= を指"
"定）、difftasticは[[*Difftastic][構造的比較]]のための外部diffコマンドとして利"
"用できます。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1524
#, no-wrap
msgid "lazygit-git"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1526
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"git = {\n"
"  overrideGpg = true;\n"
"  pagers = [\n"
"    {\n"
"      colorArg = \"always\";\n"
"      pager = \"delta --dark --paging=never\";\n"
"    }\n"
"    {\n"
"      externalDiffCommand = \"difft --color=always\";\n"
"    }\n"
"  ];\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1540
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fish Abbreviations"
msgstr "Fishの略語"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1542
msgid ""
"Shell abbreviations for frequent git operations. Abbreviations (not aliases) "
"are used because fish expands them inline before execution, making the "
"actual command visible in history and allowing modification before running."
msgstr ""
"頻繁に使うgit操作のシェル略語です。エイリアスではなく略語を使用しているのは、"
"fishが実行前にインラインで展開するため、履歴に実際のコマンドが表示され、実行"
"前の修正も可能になるためです。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1546
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-fish-abbreviations"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1548
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"programs.fish.shellAbbrs = {\n"
"  <<git-abbr-push>>\n"
"  <<git-abbr-pull>>\n"
"  <<git-abbr-commit>>\n"
"  <<git-abbr-status>>\n"
"  <<git-abbr-stash>>\n"
"  <<git-abbr-switch>>\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1558
#, no-wrap
msgid "Push"
msgstr "Push"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1560
msgid ""
"Force push with lease — safer than =--force= as it prevents overwriting "
"remote changes not yet fetched."
msgstr ""
"lease付きの強制プッシュです。まだfetchされていないリモートの変更の上書きを防"
"ぐため、=--force= よりも安全です。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1563
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-abbr-push"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1565
#, no-wrap
msgid "gpf = \"git push --force-with-lease\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1568
#, no-wrap
msgid "Pull"
msgstr "Pull"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1570
msgid ""
"=gpm= pulls from the remote's default branch, dynamically detected via =git "
"remote show= rather than hardcoding =main= or =master=. This handles "
"repositories that still use =master= or other branch naming conventions."
msgstr ""
"=gpm= はリモートのデフォルトブランチからpullします。=main= や =master= をハー"
"ドコードするのではなく、=git remote show= で動的に検出します。これにより"
"=master= や他のブランチ命名規約を使用するリポジトリにも対応できます。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1574
msgid ""
"=gpu= pulls from upstream — used in fork workflows to sync with the original "
"repository."
msgstr ""
"=gpu= はupstreamからpullします。フォークワークフローでオリジナルのリポジトリ"
"と同期するために使用されます。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1576
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-abbr-pull"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1578
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gpm = \"git pull (git remote show origin | sed -n '/HEAD branch/s/.*: //p')\";\n"
"gpu = \"git pull upstream\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1582
#, no-wrap
msgid "Commit"
msgstr "Commit"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1584
msgid ""
"=gci= creates a commit. The trailing space allows directly appending =-m "
"\"message\"=."
msgstr ""
"=gci= はコミットを作成します。末尾のスペースにより =-m \"message\"= を直接追"
"加できます。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1586
msgid ""
"=gca= amends the last commit, frequently used during interactive rebase "
"workflows."
msgstr ""
"=gca= は直前のコミットを修正します。インタラクティブrebaseのワークフローで頻"
"繁に使用されます。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1588
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-abbr-commit"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1590
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gci = \"git commit \";\n"
"gca = \"git commit --amend\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1594
#, no-wrap
msgid "Status"
msgstr "Status"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1596
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-abbr-status"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1598
#, no-wrap
msgid "gs = \"git status\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1601
#, no-wrap
msgid "Stash"
msgstr "Stash"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1603
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-abbr-stash"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1605
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gst = \"git stash\";\n"
"gstp = \"git stash pop\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1609
#, no-wrap
msgid "Switch"
msgstr "Switch"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1611
#, no-wrap
msgid "git-abbr-switch"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1613
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gsw = \"git switch\";\n"
"gswc = \"git switch -c\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading *
#: modules/configuration.org:1617
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Zen Browser"
msgid "Browser"
msgstr "Zen Browser"

#. type: heading **
#: modules/configuration.org:1619
#, no-wrap
msgid "Zen Browser"
msgstr "Zen Browser"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1621
msgid ""
"[[https://zen-browser.app/][Zen Browser]] is a Firefox-based browser with a "
"focus on privacy and customization.  Firefox derivatives were preferred over "
"Chromium-based browsers because Firefox's extension ecosystem and "
"=about:config= provide deeper control over browser behavior, and the Nix "
"ecosystem has mature tooling for managing Firefox profiles declaratively via "
"home-manager."
msgstr ""
"[[https://zen-browser.app/][Zen Browser]]はプライバシーとカスタマイズに焦点を"
"当てたFirefoxベースのブラウザです。Firefoxの拡張機能エコシステムと "
"=about:config= がブラウザの動作をより深く制御でき、NixエコシステムにはFirefox"
"のプロファイルをhome-managerで宣言的に管理する成熟したツールがあるため、"
"ChromiumベースのブラウザよりFirefox派生が選ばれました。"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1626
msgid ""
"Zen Browser was chosen over vanilla Firefox for its improved UI/UX while "
"retaining full Firefox compatibility — extensions, search engines, and "
"profile settings work identically."
msgstr ""
"Zen Browserは、Firefoxの完全な互換性を保ちつつUI/UXが改善されているため、素の"
"Firefoxより選ばれました。拡張機能、検索エンジン、プロファイル設定は同じように"
"動作します。"

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1635
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  inputs,\n"
"  config,\n"
"  lib,\n"
"  pkgs,\n"
"  ...\n"
"}:\n"
"let\n"
"  cfg = config.my.programs.zen-browser;\n"
"in\n"
"{\n"
"  imports = [ inputs.zen-browser.homeModules.beta ];"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1648
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"options.my.programs.zen-browser = {\n"
"  enable = lib.mkEnableOption \"Zen Browser\";\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1652
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"config = lib.mkIf cfg.enable {\n"
"  programs.zen-browser = {\n"
"    enable = true;\n"
"    profiles.natsukium = {\n"
"      <<zen-browser-settings>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1658
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<zen-browser-search>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1660
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"        <<zen-browser-extensions>>\n"
"      };\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1667
#, no-wrap
msgid "Settings"
msgstr "設定"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1669
msgid ""
"Auto-install extensions without user prompts. By default, Firefox shows a "
"confirmation dialog for each extension installed via the profile. Setting "
"=extensions.autoDisableScopes= to 0 disables this behavior, which is "
"necessary for fully declarative extension management — otherwise the first "
"launch after a profile rebuild would require manual approval for every "
"extension."
msgstr ""
"ユーザープロンプトなしで拡張機能を自動インストールします。デフォルトでは、"
"Firefoxはプロファイル経由でインストールされる各拡張機能に確認ダイアログを表示"
"します。=extensions.autoDisableScopes= を0に設定するとこの動作が無効になり、"
"完全に宣言的な拡張機能管理に必要です。そうしないと、プロファイル再ビルド後の"
"初回起動時にすべての拡張機能について手動承認が必要になります。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1675
#, no-wrap
msgid "zen-browser-settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1677
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"settings = {\n"
"  \"extensions.autoDisableScopes\" = 0;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1682
#, no-wrap
msgid "Search Engines"
msgstr "検索エンジン"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1684
msgid ""
"Custom search engines for quick access to development-related package "
"registries and documentation. Each engine is assigned a short alias (e.g., "
"=@np=) for use in the address bar, avoiding the need to navigate to each "
"site manually."
msgstr ""
"開発関連のパッケージレジストリやドキュメントに素早くアクセスするためのカスタ"
"ム検索エンジンです。各エンジンには短いエイリアス（例: =@np=）が割り当てられて"
"おり、アドレスバーで使用でき、各サイトに手動で移動する必要がなくなります。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1688
#, no-wrap
msgid "zen-browser-search"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1690
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"search = {\n"
"  force = true;\n"
"  engines = {\n"
"    <<zen-browser-search-engine-nix-packages>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1695
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<zen-browser-search-engine-nixos-wiki>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1697
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<zen-browser-search-engine-noogle>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1699
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<zen-browser-search-engine-crates-io>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1701
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<zen-browser-search-engine-npm>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1703
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <<zen-browser-search-engine-pypi>>\n"
"  };\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1708
#, no-wrap
msgid "Nix Packages"
msgstr "Nixパッケージ"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1710
msgid ""
"Search the official NixOS/nixpkgs repository. Uses =nixos-icons= from "
"nixpkgs for the icon to avoid depending on an external URL that could change "
"or become unavailable."
msgstr ""
"公式のNixOS/nixpkgsリポジトリを検索します。変更や利用不能になる可能性のある外"
"部URLに依存しないよう、アイコンにはnixpkgsの=nixos-icons= を使用しています。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1713
#, no-wrap
msgid "zen-browser-search-engine-nix-packages"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1715
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"nix-packages = {\n"
"  name = \"Nix Packages\";\n"
"  urls = [\n"
"    {\n"
"      template = \"https://search.nixos.org/packages\";\n"
"      params = [\n"
"        {\n"
"          name = \"type\";\n"
"          value = \"packages\";\n"
"        }\n"
"        {\n"
"          name = \"query\";\n"
"          value = \"{searchTerms}\";\n"
"        }\n"
"      ];\n"
"    }\n"
"  ];"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1733
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  icon = \"${pkgs.nixos-icons}/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/nix-snowflake.svg\";\n"
"  definedAliases = [ \"@np\" ];\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1738
#, no-wrap
msgid "NixOS Wiki"
msgstr "NixOS Wiki"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1740
msgid ""
"Search the NixOS community wiki for configuration examples and "
"troubleshooting guides."
msgstr ""
"NixOSコミュニティwikiで設定例やトラブルシューティングガイドを検索します。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1742
#, no-wrap
msgid "zen-browser-search-engine-nixos-wiki"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1744
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"nixos-wiki = {\n"
"  name = \"NixOS Wiki\";\n"
"  urls = [ { template = \"https://wiki.nixos.org/w/index.php?search={searchTerms}\"; } ];\n"
"  icon = \"https://wiki.nixos.org/favicon.ico\";\n"
"  definedAliases = [ \"@nw\" ];\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1752
#, no-wrap
msgid "noogle"
msgstr "noogle"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1754
msgid ""
"[[https://noogle.dev/][noogle]] is a Nix function search engine — the "
"equivalent of Hoogle for Haskell.  Useful for discovering library functions "
"by type signature or name when writing Nix expressions."
msgstr ""
"[[https://noogle.dev/][noogle]]はNix関数の検索エンジンで、Haskellにおける"
"Hoogleに相当します。Nix式を書く際に型シグネチャや名前でライブラリ関数を見つけ"
"るのに便利です。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1757
#, no-wrap
msgid "zen-browser-search-engine-noogle"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1759
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"noogle = {\n"
"  name = \"noogle\";\n"
"  urls = [ { template = \"https://noogle.dev/q?term={searchTerms}\"; } ];\n"
"  icon = \"https://noogle.dev/favicon.png\";\n"
"  definedAliases = [ \"@noogle\" ];\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1767
#, no-wrap
msgid "crates.io"
msgstr "crates.io"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1769
msgid ""
"Search the Rust package registry for crate discovery and version information."
msgstr "Rustパッケージレジストリでcrateの検索とバージョン情報を調べます。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1771
#, no-wrap
msgid "zen-browser-search-engine-crates-io"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1773
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"crates-io = {\n"
"  name = \"crates.io\";\n"
"  urls = [ { template = \"https://crates.io/search?q={searchTerms}\"; } ];\n"
"  icon = \"https://crates.io/favicon.ico\";\n"
"  definedAliases = [ \"@crates\" ];\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1781
#, no-wrap
msgid "npm"
msgstr "npm"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1783
msgid "Search the npm registry for JavaScript/TypeScript package discovery."
msgstr "npmレジストリでJavaScript/TypeScriptパッケージを検索します。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1785
#, no-wrap
msgid "zen-browser-search-engine-npm"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1787
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"npm = {\n"
"  name = \"npm\";\n"
"  urls = [ { template = \"https://www.npmjs.com/search?q={searchTerms}\"; } ];\n"
"  icon = \"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=npmjs.com&sz=64\";\n"
"  definedAliases = [ \"@npm\" ];\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ****
#: modules/configuration.org:1795
#, no-wrap
msgid "PyPI"
msgstr "PyPI"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1797
msgid "Search the Python Package Index for Python package discovery."
msgstr "Python Package IndexでPythonパッケージを検索します。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1799
#, no-wrap
msgid "zen-browser-search-engine-pypi"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1801
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"pypi = {\n"
"  name = \"PyPI\";\n"
"  urls = [ { template = \"https://pypi.org/search/?q={searchTerms}\"; } ];\n"
"  icon = \"https://pypi.org/favicon.ico\";\n"
"  definedAliases = [ \"@pypi\" ];\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. type: heading ***
#: modules/configuration.org:1809
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extensions"
msgstr "拡張機能"

#. type: paragraph
#: modules/configuration.org:1811
msgid ""
"Browser extensions managed declaratively. Extensions are sourced from two "
"overlay-provided sets: =firefox-addons= (from the NUR firefox-addons "
"repository) and =my-firefox-addons= (custom additions not available "
"upstream)."
msgstr ""
"宣言的に管理されるブラウザ拡張機能です。拡張機能は2つのoverlayで提供される"
"セットから取得されます。=firefox-addons=（NUR firefox-addonsリポジトリから）"
"と =my-firefox-addons=（アップストリームにないカスタムの追加）です。"

#. type: keyword NAME
#: modules/configuration.org:1815
#, no-wrap
msgid "zen-browser-extensions"
msgstr ""

#. type: paragraph in src
#: modules/configuration.org:1817
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"extensions = {\n"
"  packages =\n"
"    (with pkgs.firefox-addons; [\n"
"      bitwarden\n"
"      instapaper-official\n"
"      keepa\n"
"      onepassword-password-manager\n"
"      refined-github\n"
"      tampermonkey\n"
"      vimium\n"
"      wayback-machine\n"
"      zotero-connector\n"
"    ])\n"
"    ++ (with pkgs.my-firefox-addons; [\n"
"      adguard-adblocker\n"
"      calilay\n"
"      kiseppe-price-chart-kindle\n"
"    ]);\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

